==English==
===Noun===
'''dork''' (''plural'' '''dorks''' also spelled ''dorque'')
Cindy Lester
#(''US, slang'') A contraction for "door key" child.  The term for a boy or girl who is (or was) left alone for long periods, locking themselves inside with little to do, isolated, possibly poor, learning little, while a single parent (or both parents) work or are away.  Origin: probably late 1930's or early 1940's US.  Compare with the more neutral sounding term "latch key children" popular with media and professionals in the 1980's.


